Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: default
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Default kSecAttrAccessible all keychain items are stored with unless otherwise specified

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: afterFirstUnlock
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can only be accessed once the device has been unlocked after a restart. This is recommended for items that need to be accesible by background applications. Items with this attribute will migrate to a new device when using encrypted backups.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: afterFirstUnlockThisDeviceOnly
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can only be accessed once the device has been unlocked after a restart. This is recommended for items that need to be accessible by background applications. Items with this attribute will never migrate to a new device, so after a backup is restored to a new device these items will be missing.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: always
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can always be accessed regardless of the lock state of the device. This is not recommended for anything except system use. Items with this attribute will migrate to a new device when using encrypted backups.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: alwaysThisDeviceOnly
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can always be accessed regardless of the lock state of the device. This option is not recommended for anything except system use. Items with this attribute will never migrate to a new device, so after a backup is restored to a new device, these items will be missing.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: whenPasscodeSetThisDeviceOnly
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can only be accessed while the device is unlocked. This is recommended for items that only need to be accessible while the application is in the foreground and requires a passcode to be set on the device. Items with this attribute will never migrate to a new device, so after a backup is restored to a new device, these items will be missing. This attribute will not be available on devices without a passcode. Disabling the device passcode will cause all previously protected items to be deleted.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: whenUnlocked
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can only be accessed while the device is unlocked. This is recommended for items that only need be accesible while the application is in the foreground. Items with this attribute will migrate to a new device when using encrypted backups.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.name: whenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html#/s:8.abstract: Item data can only be accessed while the device is unlocked. This is recommended for items that only need be accesible while the application is in the foreground. Items with this attribute will never migrate to a new device, so after a backup is restored to a new device, these items will be missing.

Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html.name: Accessibility
Classes/Keychain/Accessibility.html.abstract: Predefined Accessibility levels used to secure Keychain items with various security levels.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC14s.name: synchronizable
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC14s.abstract: Synchronizable indicates whether the Keychain in question is synchronized to other devices through iCloud. Any operation made with a Keychain where synchronizable is true will be synced accross all iCloud devices connected to the user’s account.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11s.name: serviceName
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11s.abstract: ServiceName is used for the kSecAttrService property to uniquely identify this keychain accessor. If no service name is specified, Keychain will default to using the bundleIdentifier.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11a.name: accessGroup
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11a.abstract: AccessGroup is used for the kSecAttrAccessGroup property to identify which Keychain Access Group this entry belongs to. This allows you to use the Keychain with shared keychain access between different applications.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11s.name: init(serviceName:accessGroup:synchronizable:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC11s.abstract: Create a new Keychain instance with a custom Service Name and optional custom access group.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC5st.name: store(_:forKey:withAccessibility:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC5st.abstract: Store a DataConvertible object to the keychain with a specified key. Any data previously saved with this key be overwritten with the new value.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC12r.name: removeObject(forKey:withAccessibility:)
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC12r.abstract: Removes an object associated with a specified key. If re-using a key but with a different accessibility, first remove the previous key value using removeObjectForKey(:withAccessibility) using the same accessibilty it was saved with.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC5pu.name: purge()
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC5pu.abstract: Removes all keychain items matching the current ServiceName and AccessGroup, if set.

Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC7al.name: allKeys()
Classes/Keychain.html#/s:8KeychainAAC7al.abstract: Get the keys of all keychain entries matching the current ServiceName and AccessGroup if one is set.
